+
+## ADR-0064 — Presentation-layer attention scoring: demote demanding-ness at the briefing lane + inbox rail, never the immutable category (resolves #210; folds in #230; Tier 2 of #218)
+
+**Decision.** Triage over-tags attention — `urgent` + `action_needed` ≈ **26%** of the inbox, suggested-todo acceptance ≈ **1%** — because the classifier decides demand from message **shape**, blind to the user's standing relative to the sender and to recurrence. The fix is a **presentation-layer attention score**: a deterministic `[0,1]` score (projected to three display bands `demanding | normal | muted`) computed at the **consumer** — the briefing lane assignment and the inbox-rail badge — from signals already on hand, that **re-ranks and visually de-emphasizes** items without ever touching the stored category. This also folds in **#230** (the briefing characterizing a busy day as "quiet"), the inverse symptom of the same "presentation doesn't reflect reality" root, served by a sibling **day-shape** signal off the ADR-0062 object-state projection.
+
+**The load-bearing invariant — the category is honest and immutable; only presentation moves.** `email_triage.category` is **never written** by this work. Triage labels are immutable (ADR-0048); the model never bends the category (ADR-0059 alt-(e) explicitly rejected "demote `awaiting_reply` by significance"; ADR-0060 m4 — only an explicit `force_category` user instruction may re-stamp, logged). A cold LinkedIn ask genuinely *is* an unanswered question — `awaiting_reply` is the honest label. "Demanding-ness" is a *ranking/display* property layered **on top of** the honest category, computed where it is consumed and thrown away after rendering — exactly the ephemerality ADR-0048 gives open-loop reconciliation.
+
+**Framing — why this resolves #210's "Direction B" without the contradiction it carried.** #210 proposed letting significance *demote the category*. Re-grilled against the locked ADRs that is a direct violation: it would have the **model's** significance read overwrite an **honest immutable** label, the one move ADR-0048/0059-(e)/0060-m4 jointly forbid. The reconciliation is a layer shift, not a behavior change: keep the honest category, move demanding-ness to the **lane + badge**. This is also why #210 is *not* a rubric-tuning problem (the repo norm "principles over exemplars" already warns off whack-a-mole prompt patches) and *not* a classifier change — the classifier keeps classifying honestly; a new read-only layer decides what gets *surfaced* as demanding.
+
+**The signal — one pure function, three read-only inputs, graceful degradation.** `attentionScore(inputs) → { score, band }` lives in `@alfred/contracts` (zero Node deps — the same web-safe home as the briefing contract, so the briefing renderer and the client rail share one scoring truth, the ADR-0048-D pattern of relocating the resolver to share one render truth). Inputs:
+
+- **Category base demand** — an intrinsic per-category weight (`urgent` > `action_needed` > `awaiting_reply` > `follow_up`/`meeting`/`payment`), `as const satisfies Record<TriageCategory, number>`. This is the **floor**: significance and recurrence move an item *within* and *down* from its category's demand, never *up* past it, and never past the security/`urgent` override floor (ADR-0051 exposed-secret pin stays demanding).
+- **Sender significance** — the **precomputed scalar** on the sender's `person` entity (`meta.significance.score`, ADR-0057/0059), bucketed at the same two cutoffs the sender-relationship resolver already uses (`0.66` / `0.33`). Read via a `getSenderSignificance(userId, email)` helper factored out of the resolver's existing entity-by-alias read path — **never recomputed** (ADR-0059 §4: the scalar is computed once, the edge lives where consumed; this is a second consumer, parallel to the todo-rubric consumer, and does **not** amend the ADR-0057 four-consumer contract). **Degrades to neutral** when the sender is unscored / non-human / has no graph row — exactly today's intrinsic-only behavior, safe by construction. The graph is live (populated by the `memory-extraction` workflow's `runSignificancePass` + the P4a backfill).
+- **Recurrence decay** — a recurring machine notification is *less* demanding each repeat (a CloudWatch `ALARM:` tagged `urgent` ten times is, to the human, the definition of *not* urgent). A windowed, cross-row property: group by `(sender, normalizedSubject)` and decay the Nth repeat. Subject normalization (strip `ALARM:`/`Re:`/digits/dates) is a shared contracts util. **Principle, not exemplar** — the rule is "recurring + bot-shaped sender decays," keyed on the same human/bulk-prior signal the classifier's over-classification net already reads, **never** a CloudWatch string match.
+
+**Architectural shape.**
+
+- **Scorer + recurrence util (`@alfred/contracts`, pure).** `attentionScore`, `normalizeSubjectForRecurrence`, the `AttentionBand` type, and the base-demand table — unit-tested (pure, deterministic; the cheap-to-cover surface). Two band cutoffs are the only numeric knobs, mirroring ADR-0059's word-bucketing precedent and folding into the same data-tuned weights item.
+- **Significance read (`@alfred/api`).** `getSenderSignificance` — one shared significance read for both the resolver and the scorer, no recompute.
+- **Briefing lane (`gather.ts` → `compose.ts`).** After the existing GitHub loop-reconciliation, score every priority item and split the priority set into a **demanding lane** (band ≥ demanding, capped) and an **ambient tail** (the rest — low-significance cold asks, recurring machine noise). Both carry their honest category unchanged. `BriefingDigest`/`BriefingGather` gain the lane split + per-item band (additive contract fields). Compose **leads** with the demanding lane and renders the tail as a terse "also happening" line — **driven off the band, never re-judged in prose** (no "if it looks like an alarm" prompt patch).
+- **Day-shape (#230).** A deterministic `dayShape` in gather off `objectStateStore.list(userId, "github", …)` + the existing `integration_activity` counts → `{ activityVolume: busy|normal|quiet, shipped: {title,url}[] }`. Compose **never** characterizes a day as "quiet" when `activityVolume !== quiet`; evening renders a "what you shipped" recap from `resolved` objects (dovetails with the existing `closedLoops` recap). This consumer was closed-as-folded-into-#212 but never built in the #212 v1; it lands here.
+- **Inbox rail (`apps/web`).** Order + visually de-emphasize by band; the badge still shows the **honest category**, a `muted` row is just dimmed. Significance isn't synced today → one **additive** synced field `senderSignificanceBand` on the triage row, written at classify time (the classifier already calls `resolveSenderRelationship`; stash the scalar's band). Recurrence is computed **client-side** by grouping the already-synced rows (the rail renders the full list) through the shared `normalizeSubjectForRecurrence` + `attentionScore` — each surface computes what it can see, off one shared formula.
+
+**Sequencing (graceful, lowest-risk-first).** **Phase A** — recurrence-decay + day-shape: **no** significance-graph dependency, buys the CloudWatch-10× and busy-day-quiet wins immediately. **Phase B** — significance-weighting layered into the same scorer + the demanding/ambient lane split. **Phase C** — the `senderSignificanceBand` synced field (`db:generate` → `db:migrate`, never `db:push`) + rail ordering/de-emphasis.
+
+**Success metric — the #210 reframe.** The metric is **not** "% of inbox tagged `urgent`/`action_needed`" — those category counts *should not move* (honest categories). It is **"% of inbox surfaced in the demanding lane / bright-vs-dimmed in the rail,"** targeted well below today's 26%, with recurring-machine and cold-low-significance items landing in the ambient tail; corroborated by suggested-todo acceptance over the following window. This is the first concrete number for the #219 drift-metrics gap.
+
+**Honors ADR-0048 / 0057 / 0059 / 0060 / 0062.** Category immutable, demotion is a render property (0048). Significance scalar consumed-not-recomputed, contract unchanged (0057/0059). Model never bends the category — only an explicit instruction may, logged (0060). Day-shape reads the deterministic object-state projection (0062).
+
+**Why.** The 26%/1% gap is structural — a significance- and recurrence-blind classifier cannot produce a calibrated demand signal no matter how the prompt is tuned. Moving demanding-ness to the presentation layer fixes it at the seam the ADRs leave open (rendering) without violating the immutable-category contract three ADRs protect; reusing the already-live significance scalar and the already-merged object-state projection means the design is *codification of locked decisions*, not new architecture; and the lane/band split is the honest expression of "this is a real `awaiting_reply` that simply does not warrant your attention right now."
+
+**Alternatives.** (a) **Let significance demote the category** (#210 Direction B as written) — rejected: the model overwriting an honest immutable label, forbidden by ADR-0048/0059-(e)/0060-m4. (b) **Tune the triage rubric / prompt** — rejected: significance + recurrence are not in the classifier's input; no prompt patch adds a signal the model can't see (and violates "principles over exemplars"). (c) **Have the classifier infer significance itself** — rejected: duplicates the ADR-0057/0059 scalar, re-introduces per-email LLM judgment of standing, and couples the honest category decision to a fuzzy read. (d) **Compute the whole score client-side** — rejected for the briefing (server has the authoritative window + significance read); retained *only* for the rail's recurrence half, which is intrinsically a client-visible grouping. (e) **Persist the full attention score on the triage row** — rejected: recurrence is a windowed property that can't be known at classify time (you don't know future repeats), so a row-frozen score would be stale; only the slow-moving `senderSignificanceBand` is persisted/synced.
+
+**Parked.** Behavioral priors (dismiss:done 41:1, archive-without-reply — ADR-0055 Loop-2) as a 4th attention input — north star, deferred; v1 inputs are category + significance + recurrence only. Recurrence beyond the gather/synced window (a persisted recurrence counter). Significance-weighting of the *todo* mint — already shipped via rubric 16b (ADR-0059), untouched here.
+
+**Open.** Base-demand weights + the two band cutoffs (seed by judgment, tune from the prod distribution — shared tuning surface with ADR-0057/0059 weights). Recurrence window vs. a short lookback query (does the 10× alarm span windows?). The ambient-tail floor (may recurrence demote `urgent`→`normal`, and never below? exposed-secret `urgent` stays pinned demanding). Eval coverage — an attention-scoring case in the `@alfred/api` evalite lane once the formula stabilizes. Plan: [docs/plans/triage-attention-demotion-v1.md](./docs/plans/triage-attention-demotion-v1.md).
